---------------------------- UNDOCUMENTED FEATURE ----------------------------
While it is not in the manual, you can turn off the music on the mission
select level by pressing the "F1" key.  Note that it does not always work.
This is a function of the original game.



-------------------------------INSTALLATION-----------------------------------

NOTE: The default ICONS are designed for WorkBench 2.0. WorkBench 1.3 ICONS are
      also included. They have "For1.3" appended to the normal name. Just
      rename and copy over the normal one to use. (All this will do is make the
      the icons look better , there are no other differences.)

                                 HARD DISK
 Move the GS2000 Upgrade to the directory in which GunShip resides.  This may
 be accomplished by either:
  A. Copying both "GunShip 2000 Upgrade" and "GunShip 2000 UpGrade.info" from
     the CLI.
  B. In workbench, open both the directory which contains the upgrade and the
     hard disk directory that contains GunShip 2000. Now use the mouse to move
     the "GunShip 2000 Upgrade" icon and drop it into the GunShip directory
     window on the hard disk.

                                   FLOPPY
 Move the GS2000 Upgrade to the GS_DSK1 disk (GunShip 2000 disk number 1).
   WARNING: use a copy , DO NOT use the original!!!
 This may be accomplished by either:
  A. Copying both "GunShip 2000 Upgrade" and "GunShip 2000 UpGrade.info" from
     the CLI.
  B. In workbench, open the directory the Upgrade is in and double click on the
     GS_DSK1 icon. Now use the mouse to move the "GunShip 2000 Upgrade" icon
     and drop it into the GS_DSK1 window.


---------------------------------- LOADING -----------------------------------
 Just click on the Icon from the workbench , or from the cli, run the file
 "GunShip 2000 Upgrade". (With quotes)


  NOTE: You may also run the Upgrade without installing it. Double click on the
        "GunShip 2000 Upgrade" icon on the original disk. You will then be
         prompted to insert "GS_DSK1". After the disk is inserted, it will
         load normally.


  NOTE: This Upgrade does not in any way change the original program. You MUST
        run the program each time by useing the IDD upgrade. If you do not ,
        none of the new features will operate.


  WARNING: A system with only one meg of ram is unlikely to able to load from
           workbench with a full system installed. In this case, you need to
           boot from a copy of the gunship 2000 disk with the GS2000 Upgrade
           icon in it. You then double click on the icon to start.
           (See floppy installation above)

--------------------------------- NEW FEATURES --------------------------------
ALL of the following NEW features for GS2000 are now available using the Amiga
Smart Port from IDD!
  1.    More sensitive control!  The GunShip 2000 upgrade makes use of the full
        range (0-251) of the AMIGA Smart Port instead of the original limited
        range provided by the game (0-40).
  2.    An Enhanced Flight Mode which yields more realistic flying.
        (Allows flying sideways or at an angle and using pedals!)
  3.    Keyboard pedal controls using the left and right arrow keys when
        in the Enhanced Flight Mode.
  4.    Auto-Sensing of the Amiga Smart Port in analog mode with automatic
        software switching between digital and analog joysticks modes.
  5.    Analog joystick will work at all levels (including menus) with
        automatic switching between digital and analog modes.
  6.    Joystick centering function provides precise centering. This feature
        can be used at anytime... Even during flight!
  7.    Dynamic Joystick Scaling - The IDD Upgrade will adjust the control
        scale to use the full capabilities of your joystick to obtain maximum
        performance simply by moving your joystick to all extremes!
  8.    Joystick Threshold Sensitivity Setting - You can use any one of three
        threshold sensitivity settings. Use the one you need to suit your
        joystick! Switch between them at any time!
  9.    Support for ANALOG PEDALS!! This feature contains the same
        centering and dynamic scaling features used with the joystick.
        Analog pedal and collective inputs can be reversed for wiring
        compatibility.
  10.   Support for ANALOG COLLECTIVE!!  Now you can quickly and easily move
        between collective settings for maximum flying advantage.
  11.   Analog joystick buttons 1 (fire) and 2 now operate as per the manual.
        (the original game has them reversed)
  12.   Users of two button joysticks or joysticks with 4 buttons can now use
        the extra buttons for multiple (selectable) functions. This reduces the
        need to go to the keyboard during battle.


